This is a short refactor task within a single subagent invocation — task tracking isn't relevant here. I'll continue the refactor reflection.

The current state is acceptable. The expression `(100 + FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_PERCENT) / 100` is a bit verbose, but using percent-based integer arithmetic is honest about the domain (insurance surcharges are stated as percentages) and avoids floating-point traps. Future tests (20% loyalty discount, 15% repeat-contract discount, 50% cursed surcharge, 30% enchantment surcharge) all use percentages too — so this percent-based representation will compose naturally.

**Refactored Code Mass (APP)**:
```
const basePremiumByItemType: Record<string, number> = {
  sword: 100, amulet: 60, staff: 80, potion: 40,
};
const FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_PERCENT = 10;
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
export const runScenario = (scenario: any): unknown => {
  const itemType = scenario.steps[0].items[0].type;
  const basePremium = basePremiumByItemType[itemType];
  const withSurcharge = Math.ceil(basePremium * (100 + FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_PERCENT) / 100);
  const premium = withSurcharge + PROCESSING_FEE;
  return { results: [{ premium }] };
};
```

